BT 1 0 0 1 0 87 Tm 12 TL /F1 9 Tf 0 0 0 rg (The Wike Singularity exponent 2.59 = 1 + 1/nu with nu = 0.6298 is the 3D Ising exponent. The alternative candidate, the 3D) Tj T* (XY universality class \(governing superconductors, superfluids, Bose-Einstein condensates\), has nu_XY = 0.6717, giving) Tj T* (exponent 1 + 1/0.6717 = 2.489. The AIIT-THRESI data at 2.59 ) Tj /F2 9 Tf (definitively rules out) Tj /F1 9 Tf ( 3D XY and confirms ) Tj /F2 9 Tf (3D Ising) Tj /F1 9 Tf ( as the) Tj T* (universality class. This distinction is physically meaningful: 3D Ising has Z_2 symmetry \(two discrete phases: coherent and) Tj T* (incoherent\), while 3D XY has U\(1\) symmetry \(a continuous circle of phases -- superconductor order parameter\). The) Tj T* (coherence/decoherence transition is a ) Tj /F2 9 Tf (switch, not a dial) Tj /F1 9 Tf (: there is a coherent phase and a decoherent phase, with no) Tj T* (intermediate continuous phase. The conformal bootstrap calculation \(Kos et al. 2016\) provides independent confirmation of) Tj T* (nu_Ising = 0.6298 +/- 0.0005, matching the AIIT-THRESI simulation to 99.9%.) Tj T* ET
