BT 1 0 0 1 0 39 Tm 12 TL /F2 9 Tf 0 0 0 rg (Why not 4D \(mean-field\):) Tj /F1 9 Tf ( Mean-field is valid when spatial fluctuations are negligible -- when the system is far from) Tj T* (gamma_c or when the spatial dimension d > d_c = 4 \(the upper critical dimension\). At d < 4 and near gamma_c, the 3D) Tj T* (Ising class applies. Biological systems at gamma_c are in 3D and in the fluctuation-dominated regime \(inside the Ginzburg) Tj T* (criterion, Paper 18\) -- 3D Ising is correct.) Tj T* ET
